.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-rag-index - Index a directory (or file) into the node-local semantic index


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel rag index  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Chunk, embed, and store the text files under  into the node-local index.

.PP
Incremental and idempotent: unchanged files are skipped by content hash, and
files deleted on disk are pruned on re-index. Binary files and noise dirs
(.git, node_modules, .venv, ...) are skipped automatically.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for index

.PP
\fB--pattern\fP=""
	Restrict indexed filenames (glob, e.g. "*.md")


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Emit machine-readable JSON

.PP
\fB--model\fP=""
	Embedding model override (default: gte-multilingual-base)

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-rag(1)\fP
